            <div corresp="#c3710f2">
                <head>Berlin, Germany.</head>
                <p>George Gregg Fuller Vice Consul, served a sixty day detail in the Dept. of State
                    beginning June 21, 1927</p>
                <p>George J. Inman, lately 3d Secy of Legin at Riga, Latvia, assigned as Foreign
                    Service Officer and Vice Consul ofisareer for the purpose of language study,
                    subject to Executive Order No. 4879 of May 8, 1929.</p>
                <p>Augustus S. Chase, lately assigned as V.C. of career at Breslau temporarily
                    returned to Berlin without further commission.</p>
                <p>John B. Faust temp. detailed to Dept. of State, July 20, 1931.</p>
